                type="document" xml:id="d710a-25">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Editor’s Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>—No official record of the substance of this conversation has been found.
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL2">Stimson</persName>’s diary entry for July 19
                    contains the following summary: “At twelve o’clock <persName corresp="#p_CL1"
                        >Lord Cherwell</persName> called, and he and <persName corresp="#p_BHH1"
                        >Bundy</persName> and I sat out under the trees and talked over S–l. He was
                    very reasonable on the subject of notification to the Russians, feeling about as
                    doubtful as we. He reported <persName corresp="#p_CWS1">Churchill</persName> as
                    being much pleased with our luncheon together last Monday [<hi rend="italic"
                        >Tuesday</hi>]<note n="1" xml:id="d710a-25fn1">See <hi rend="italic"
                            >ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_47">p. 47</ref>.</note> and much cheered by
                    the talk.”</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
